        "title": "fix(config): warn on large memory watch FD risk",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- re-add the gateway memory-watch FD warning after #89246 reverted the earlier warning-only PR\n- keep memory watching enabled by default, but warn only when the relevant memory directories contain more than 2,000 markdown files\n- bound the startup directory scan by streaming entries and stopping after 20,000 scanned entries\n- add validation-policy coverage for local/remote gateway behavior, disabled watch, per-agent overrides, and the large-memory threshold\n\n## Related\n\n- Replaces the warning behavior reverted by #89246.\n- Follow-up to #89185, but now self-contained because #89185 was reverted.\n- Refs #86613, where FD pressure was reproduced with large watched memory trees.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/config/validation.ts src/config/validation.policy.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/config/validation.policy.test.ts`\n- local scan benchmark for 20,000 temp markdown files: about 13-15 ms per bounded scan on this machine\n",
